post_text:
Update: GBCS Re-Entry Plan

August 13, 2020
Based on New Jersey Governor Phil Murphy’s August 12 announcement that school districts may delay in-person learning related to concerns about safety standards, Greater Brunswick Charter School's Board of Trustees has authorized a plan to be submitted to the NJDOE that educates students through the Distance Learning model for the first four months of the 2020-2021 school year. This plan will follow Phase 1A - School Wide Full Distance Learning, as described in our Re-Entry Plan.

A decision regarding the learning model for January will be made at a future date.

We look forward to in-person teaching and learning, when it is safe to do so. Until then, our staff is busy designing rigorous distance learning practices that will increase student engagement, develop valuable real-time interactions, guide achievement, and more!

All the best,
Vanessa Jones
Education Director

Como probablemente sepa, la gran mayoría del personal de NBFPL fue despedido a partir del 10 de abril, por lo que los servicios de biblioteca fueron muy limitados durante los últimos cuatro meses. Nos complace decir que el personal ahora está volviendo a trabajar en fases para reintroducir servicios de la biblioteca que podamos ofrecer durante estas circunstancias extraordinarias. Agradecemos su paciencia durante este tiempo de transición y planificación. Estén atentos para más información y anuncios, ¡próximamente!

Si su arrendador o casero lo deja fuera de su casa o lo desaloja, sin una orden de la corte, o si su arrendador le quita los servicios públicos o hace otras cosas para intentar que se vaya, debe llamar a la policía de inmediato.También debe llamar a un abogado privado o comunicarse con la oficina regional de Servicios Legales. La ley dice que la policía debe asegurarse de que regrese a su departamento/casa. Los policías no pueden desalojar a los inquilinos.
Para mas información sobre evicciones y desalojos, visite
https://www.lsnjlaw.org/Housing/Landlord-Tenant/Evictions/Pages/Right-Court-Process.aspx

post_text:
f you are locked out or evicted by your landlord and not by a special court officer, or if your landlord shuts off your utilities or does other things to try to make you leave, you should call the police immediately. (You should also call a private attorney or contact your regional Legal Services office.) The law says that the police must make sure you get back into your apartment. Police officers cannot evict tenants.”

For more information on self-help, evictions read: https://www.lsnjlaw.org/Housing/Landlord-Tenant/Evictions/Pages/Right-Court-Process.aspx

post_text: Congratulations, Mayrin Reyes-Jackson, GBCS 5th grade student!
shared_text:
Conserve Wildlife Foundation of NJ
June 16 at 8:30 AM ·

We’re honoring the 5th grade winners of our #SpeciesOnTheEdge Art and Essay Contest with a virtual art show this year! Keep an eye out here on our Facebook page to see all 20 winners who were selected from over 3,000 entries across the state.

Today, we're celebrating Mayrin Reyes-Jackson from Greater Brunswick Charter School in Middlesex County for advocating for the blue-spotted salamander through an outstanding essay and original art piece.

Writing as the blue-spotted salamander in her essay, Mayrin tells us, “Hi there! I’m a blue-spotted salamander. I’m not a very well-known animal, so you probably don’t know that much about me. Sadly, my family has been endangered since 1974 because of those evil humans cutting down our trees!”

We would like to thank the PSEG Foundation, NJEA, Church & Dwight, GAF, Atlantic City Electric, Phillips 66, and Zoological Society of New Jersey for their generous support of this program.

#CWF #CWFArtShow #NJStemTogether

post_text:
Los últimos meses han sido muy difíciles para la mayoría de nosotros. Además de navegar la pandemia, ahora estamos tratando de procesar los eventos de este fin de semana, encendidos por el racismo sistémico y la injusticia social.

Por favor cree espacios seguros para que los niños expresen lo que sienten. Apoye y aliente a sus hijos a encontrar formas pacíficas y seguras de protestar y compartir sus voces.

Continúen hablando y escuchándose unos a otros. Tenga conversaciones abiertas sobre el racismo institucional, la injusticia social y todas las formas en que somos iguales como seres humanos. Avancemos juntos.

Utilice este recurso para apoyar estas conversaciones cruciales:

https://www.embracerace.org/resources/26-childrens-books-to-support-conversations-on-race-racism-resistance?fbclid=IwAR1aFXB3SnScq69WCULho1I7bbMy7p7SqJLtba1VTUTfIjoeqg_eD4TttLo

The past few months have been very difficult for most of us. In addition to navigating the pandemic, we are now trying to process the events of this weekend, ignited by systemic racism and social injustice.

Please create safe spaces for children to express what they are feeling. Please support and encourage students to find peaceful and safe ways to protest and share their voices.

Continue talking with one another and listening. Have open conversations about institutional racism, social injustice, and all the ways we are alike as human beings. Let's move forward, together.

Please use this resource to support these crucial conversations:

Yearbook Donations: Consider a gift to GBCS today!

During this spring season, when the school year is being completed through distance learning, we are making sure everyone can still receive a bit of normalcy with memories from a yearbook.

A $225 donation guarantees a class set of yearbooks, allowing each student to reflect and celebrate their learning and relationships.

Every gift, no matter the amount, makes a difference and helps to put yearbooks in the hands of our students. Join us with a gift of any size today.

If you are ordering an ad, you can also pay for it here. Just make sure to mention it is for an ad when submitting.

Thank you for your generosity during this time!
Click the link below to make a donation

NBFPL.ORG
New Brunswick Free Public Library

Robert Belvin shared a link to the group: New Brunswick New Jersey : That was then, This is now.
April 14 at 11:33 AM ·

Online at the New Brunswick Public Library

Going over the statistics for first quarter online usage and thought I would remind you all about some of the resources available by going to https://www.nbfpl.org/online-resources

Check out [I know, bad play on words] TumbleBooks, which has picture books, songs, and videos for children. In March there were over 1,000 uses.

If you want to know what happened two years ago on this date or how New Brunswick coped with the 1918 pandemic, check out both our digitized newspapers and the Proquest Digitized Newspapers. There were almost 7,500 searches for the first quarter of 2020.

I don't have the stats for Hoopla and eLibraryNJ (we get the service through our consortium) but I have been borrowing both books and audio-books to read and listen on my phone.

We may be closed but NBFPL is still trying to serve the community.

shared_text:
Greater Brunswick Charter School
March 27 at 8:15 AM ·

From Ms. Rina: Our first butterfly hatched this morning!

Last fall our students collected caterpillars from parsley and fennel plants. We put them in our portable butterfly house and fed them. The chrysalises wintered over in my garage and now they are ready to welcome spring!

De la Sra. Rina: Nuestra primera mariposa salió del capullo esta mañana!

El otoño pasado, nuestros estudiantes recolectaron orugas del perejil y plantas de hinojo. Los pusimos en nuestra casa de mariposas portátil y los alimentamos. ¡Las crisálidas pasaron el invierno en mi garaje y ahora están listas para recibir la primavera!

¿Cuánto tiempo estará cerrada la escuela?

GBCS practicará la educación a distancia a partir del lunes 16 de marzo y continuará hasta que el gobernador Murphy nos informe que es seguro reabrir. Es probable que cerremos por un mínimo de cuatro semanas, lo que los CDC recomiendan para las escuelas. Esto es deacuerdo con la orden del Gobernador Murphy el cual ordenó de que se cierren todos los edificios escolares públicos y privados mientras trabajamos para minimizar la propagación de COVID-19. Todo el personal de GBCS está trabajando de forma virtual, solo nuestro personal de servicio de alimentos y los custodios estarán en el edificio, cuando sea necesario.

By Governor Murphy’s Executive Order # 104, signed Monday, March 16, 2020,

“All public, private, and parochial preschool program premises, and elementary and secondary schools, including charter and renaissance schools, shall be closed to students beginning on Wednesday, March 18, 2020, and shall remain closed as long as this Order remains in effect.”

What that means is we do not a specific end date to our closure. We will wait until the governor changes this order to transition back to our typical school program.

shared_text:
Governor Phil Murphy
March 21 at 1:20 PM ·

BREAKING: I just signed an Executive Order directing nearly all residents to STAY AT HOME.

ALL gatherings are canceled.

ALL non-essential retail businesses must indefinitely close their physical stores to the public effective 9:00 p.m. tonight.

More: covid19.nj.gov

New Jerseyans can still take a walk outside, go buy groceries, or get take-out from a local restaurant.

But, otherwise, STAY AT HOME.

This is a time for us all to come together to flatten the curve, slow, and eventually halt the spread of #COVID19.

Only critical businesses may remain open:
🍞Grocery stores
🍎Food banks
💊Pharmacies
🩹Medical supply stores
⛽Gas stations
🏦Banks
🐶Pet supply stores
🍽️Restaurants and bars providing take-out and delivery only

For a complete list of businesses allowed to remain open, visit covid19.nj.gov

ALL other retail businesses must close, and all businesses must move to 100% work-from-home wherever possible.

Hospitals and health care facilities will remain open.

Essential public health, safety, and social services will remain accessible.

To support families unexpectedly at home, on March 13 we announced our plan to ship 10,000 free cooking kits to enrich kids bellies and minds! That same day, due to the incredible response from families, we increased that number to 25,000 free cooking kits. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
TODAY we are thrilled to announce that we are giving away an *additional* 25,000 free cooking kits -- bringing the grand total to 50,000!⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Click this link to learn more and get your kit -> raddishkids.com/suddenlyhomeschooling
⁣⁣
From our family to yours, we wish you good health and happy memories in the kitchen.⁣⁣ ❤️
⁣
#raddishkids #radkidscook #imadethismoment #suddenlyhomeschooling⁣

shared_text:
Mike Noordzy was live.
March 18 at 12:59 PM ·

for all my musician friends getting sick of shedding to the ireal backing track, I'm gonna be walking bass lines on fb live everyday from 1pm-2pm est. Tune in and and workout. I won't be able to hear you but it's great opportunity to practice melodies, comping, soloing etc with another a human (that's me).
Tunes:
1:00-1:10 Bb Blues
1:10-1:20 All the things you are
1:20-1:30 Body and Soul
1:30-1:40 Out of Nowhere
1:40-1:50 Triste (Bb)
1:50-2pm Just Friends (F)
feel free to reach out with comments, questions, ideas, requests and if you enjoy please share

and....not doing this for the money, and i know everyone is broke and gig-less but if you're feeling generous you can donate to venmo: Mike-Noordzy or PayPal MikeNoordzy@gmail.com, no amount too small, or if you dig just share with anyone who you think may enjoy

shared_text:
Mindfulness Master
March 17 at 4:01 AM ·

“And the people stayed home.
And read books, and listened, and rested, and exercised, and made art, and played games, and learned new ways of being, and were still.
And listened more deeply. Some meditated, some prayed, some danced. Some met their shadows.
And the people began to think differently.
And the people healed.
And, in the absence of people living in ignorant, dangerous, mindless, and heartless ways, the earth began to heal.
And when the danger passed, and the people joined together again, they grieved their losses, and made new choices, and dreamed new images, and created new ways to live and heal the earth fully, as they had been healed."
~ Kitty O'Meara 🙏💗✌

La Educación a Distancia ha empezado!
Nuestros maestros y estudiantes se han conectado a salones virtuales desde el Lunes. Los estudiantes terminaron sus deberes escolares, los maestros les respondieron y dieron su opinión, los padres enviaron correos a los maestros con preguntas, los maestros llamaron a los alumnos y a sus padres para ofrecer apoyo, vieron videos de las lecciones, hubo lectura en voz alta, eso y mucho mas!

Continuemos trabajando juntos!
Nuestro personal esta para apoyarles, no dude en contactarlos! Estamos a un correo electrónico de distancia.
Los correos electrónicos de nuestro personal están puestos en nuestra página de internet:
www.greaterbrunswick.org

.
